-- Mediobanca's Nagel May Replace UniCredit CEO Profumo, Repubblica Reports
-- B y   A n d r e w   D a v i s
-- 2010-09-21T06:15:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/mediobanca-s-nagel-may-replace-unicredit-ceo-profumo-repubblica-reports.html
Mediobanca SpA Chief Executive
Officer Alberto Nagel is one of the candidates to replace
UniCredit SpA CEO Alessandro Profumo should he be forced to
resign, la Repubblica reported today, without saying where it
got the information.  Other candidates to replace Profumo include Andrea Orcel,
Bank of America Corp. Merrill Lynch’s executive chairman of
global banking and markets; Giampiero Auletta Armenise, former
CEO of Unione di Banche Italiane Scpa; and Enrico Tomaso
Cucchiani, a board member of Allianz SE, one of UniCredit’s
biggest shareholders, the paper reported.  UniCredit’s board holds a special meeting today to discuss
Profumo’s future.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Davis in Rome at 
 abdavis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
